  "description": "The dish is layered like a proper home-style lunch, with acidity, spice, and texture tuned for a satisfying but lighter plate. Curry Leaf Thuvaiyal Rice Bowl brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Roast the pulse accent and chillies in a small pan on medium-low heat until fragrant. Add the vegetable if it benefits from wilting or softening and cook until concentrated.",
    "Grind with tamarind, coconut, salt, and a little water into a thick paste.",
    "Warm the paste briefly in the pan with 1 tsp oil if you want a mellower flavor, then toss through the cooked grain or serve it in a thick layer over the grain bowl.",
    "Let the bowl stand 2 minutes before eating so the paste seasons the grain evenly."
  ],
